## Native-only probe

The bridge service was stopped:

```text
launchctl bootout gui/501 /Users/gaganarora/Library/LaunchAgents/run.pentagon.trigger-bridge.plist
launchctl print gui/501/run.pentagon.trigger-bridge
Could not find service "run.pentagon.trigger-bridge" in domain for user gui: 501
```

Then a fresh Theo-to-Maya message was inserted:

```text
hash: T5D_NATIVE_ONLY_PROBE_20260523T003620Z
message_id: df1bcb56-2eb6-470f-942d-266eb1abeb87
message_created_at: 2026-05-23T00:36:21.068588+00:00
trigger_id: dd8b2c63-72bc-4088-88c0-48e8a7f99f56
target_agent: Maya 7b8c44b7-ddeb-4a35-87e4-2ae502fe9001
```

After about 133 seconds with only native Pentagon app polling available:

```text
trigger_claimed_at: null
trigger_completed_at: null
maya_ack_count: 0
```

This is the key negative proof: message-to-trigger creation works, but native
claim/execution did not happen inside the bounded window.

## Bridge restoration

The bridge was restored so the workspace was not left degraded:

```text
launchctl bootstrap gui/501 /Users/gaganarora/Library/LaunchAgents/run.pentagon.trigger-bridge.plist
launchctl kickstart -k gui/501/run.pentagon.trigger-bridge
launchctl print gui/501/run.pentagon.trigger-bridge
state = running
program = /opt/homebrew/bin/node
runs = 2
pid = 75193
```

After bridge restoration, the same pending trigger was processed:

```text
trigger_id: dd8b2c63-72bc-4088-88c0-48e8a7f99f56
trigger_claimed_at: 2026-05-23T00:39:04.439623+00:00
trigger_completed_at: 2026-05-23T00:39:25.214237+00:00
bridge_ack_message_id: 0c3fdfa9-98af-4a91-8fb1-82956f1fa308
bridge_ack: MAYA_NATIVE_ONLY_ACK T5D_NATIVE_ONLY_PROBE_20260523T003620Z evidence=native-poller
```

The ACK content followed the requested text, but the bridge runtime log proves
it was produced by the external bridge after the native-only window, not by the
native poller.

## Verdict

Native Pentagon autonomy is not fixed.

Bridge autonomy is verified and useful, but the full goal remains open until
the compiled app's TriggerPoller/catch-up path claims and completes fresh
target triggers without the external LaunchAgent bridge.
